### Summary of My FY24 Q4 Scorecard

In FY24 Q4, I made significant strides in enhancing the automation and efficiency of the PACT team. I collaborated with QA testers to establish a code-sharing repository, which is crucial for streamlining our automation efforts. By providing feedback on AI usage and developing new KPIs, I aimed to quantify the impact of PACT consultations. Additionally, I created an Automation Potential Pyramid to guide future automation initiatives, demonstrating my proactive approach to identifying areas for improvement.

I also focused on centralizing metrics and communication within the team. I developed a centralized metrics page for Pathfinder and initiated email blasts to keep stakeholders informed about automation usage. My efforts included sending a PACT QA Tester to consult on live service MLB automation, showcasing my commitment to team development and knowledge sharing. Furthermore, I actively participated in meetings with management to advocate for the full utilization of Pathfinder and support the shift-left initiative.

Financially, my contributions led to impressive efficiency gains. I supported a PACT tester in increasing efficiencies from $56k over seven months to $105k over five months. The cumulative usage of MLB Pathfinder reached 3,329 hours, resulting in a cumulative efficiency of $74,739 by the end of Q3. My guidance helped the Chaos project achieve significant automation reinvestment, further underscoring the financial impact of my initiatives.

Innovation was a key theme in my scorecard, as I leveraged AI to create test cases, analyze call stacks, and automate various processes. I maintained automated bridges to enhance communication about bugs and issues, which increased our team's response time and visibility on development challenges. My work in developing the QA task issue type has also improved our efficiency in tracking and assigning tasks.

I continued to focus on the development of my team members, providing mentorship and guidance to help them grow their skills. I held regular one-on-one meetings to enhance their knowledge of JIRA, Testrail, and Confluence. Additionally, I assigned engineering tools like Pathfinder and AI to testers, encouraging them to explore possible uses and become key sources of knowledge.

Throughout the quarter, I actively researched AI usage and machine learning to identify practical applications for our work. I also created assessments and objectives for the PACT team to help spread automation across the test floor. My efforts in maintaining the automated geekbot tool in Slack facilitated weekly reports and standups, keeping our team aligned and informed.

Finally, I expanded the PACT team by adding new QA testers and Sr. Testers, enhancing our talent pool for future projects. I connected QA testers with engineers to learn automation using in-house tools, and I created documents to teach JQL and AI usage. Overall, my focus on innovation, team development, and financial efficiency has positioned the PACT team for continued success.
